Preheat your oven to 180°C and put a large #saucepan{} of @water{some} with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the potatoes. Peel and chop the @sweet potato{1}(peeled and chopped into 2cm chunks) and @baking potato{1}(peeled and chopped into 2cm chunks). Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Add the potatoes to the boiling water and simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> The potatoes are ready when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Meanwhile, remove and discard the plastic film from the @Linda McCartney sausages{6}. Drizzle the sausages with @oil{some} in their #aluminium tray{}, turning to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until browned and piping hot, ~{16-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> The sausages are cooked when piping hot.

While the sausages cook, heat a splash of @oil{some} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and cook until soft, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring often.

When your sausages have been in for about ~{5%minutes}, add the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} to another #baking tray{}. Drizzle on a little @oil{some} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on the middle shelf for the remaining time, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> The broccoli should be tender and slightly crispy.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain them in a #colander{} set over a bowl or jug to reserve some of the water so you can use it for the gravy. Return the cooked potatoes to the original saucepan, add a knob of @butter{some} (or plant based butter if you'd prefer) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then cover with a lid to keep warm.

Once the onion is soft, add the @balsamic vinegar{2%tbsp}, stir together and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the reserved potato water (see ingredients for amount) to the pan with the onion along with the @red wine stock paste{28%g}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until your gravy has reduced and thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Simply add a splash more water if it gets too thick.

Serve the veggie sausages on top of a large helping of mash, with some red onion gravy spooned over and the tenderstem broccoli alongside. Enjoy!